pr_review_comment_body:
That's a good argument against `**kwargs`, you've convinced me :wink:

I still would prefer an immutable default parameter because it's much more maintainable. All it takes is one mistaken change in the future and it'll blow up on you.
What I usually do is set the default to `None` and then check for that in the body of the method:

```python
def declare_exchange(self, ..., arguments=None):
    if arguments is None:
        arguments = {}
    ...
```

Simplify the logic here. If you have used global_pool, there is no need to check the stride, kernel or pad.
```c++
if(! param.global_pool) {
// CHECK kernel, pad, stride
}
```

